cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning to learn complex tasks efficiently, particularly when the task is learned from raw observations such as images. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and systems and control (cs.SY). Among these, machine learning (cs.LG) is the most likely category, as the paper focuses on the use of reinforcement learning to learn tasks efficiently. Robotics (cs.RO) is also a likely category, as the paper evaluates the method on a real-world robot. Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is another possible category, as the paper discusses the use of unsupervised interaction with the environment to learn dynamical distances. Computer vision (cs.CV) is also a possible category, as the paper mentions the use of raw image observations. Finally, systems and control (cs.SY) is a less likely category, but still possible given the focus on dynamical distances as a measure of expected time to reach a goal state.
